.TH "write_scratchpad" 9 "write_scratchpad" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
write_scratchpad \- write nb_bytes in the device RAM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" write_scratchpad
.BI "(struct w1_slave *sl "  ","
.BI "const u8 *data "  ","
.BI "u8 nb_bytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sl" 12
pointer to the slave to write in
.IP "data" 12
pointer to an array of 3 bytes, as 3 bytes MUST be written
.IP "nb_bytes" 12
number of bytes to be written (2 for DS18S20, 3 otherwise)
.SH "RETURN"
0 if success, -kernel error code otherwise
